  "prompt": "Why did the Philippine president Rodrigo Duterte call Barack Obama a \"son of a bitch\"?",
  "response": "In 2016, prior to a planned meeting at an ASEAN summit in Laos, Rodrigo Duterte made a statement to reporters in which he used the phrase \"son of a bitch\" in response to concerns that Obama would raise the issue of extrajudicial killings in the Philippines' war on drugs.\n\nDuterte's specific words were: \"I am a president of a sovereign state and we have long ceased to be a colony. I do not have any master except the Filipino people, nobody else. You must be respectful. Do not just throw questions. Putang ina, I will swear at you in that forum.\" \"Putang ina\" is a Tagalog phrase that can be translated as \"son of a bitch.\"\n\nThe White House subsequently canceled the planned meeting between the two leaders.\n",
